ProcedureHelp.#cdata:
Syntax: PROC HPCANDISC <options> ;     
    BY variables ; 
    CLASS variable ; 
    FREQ variable ;
    ID variables; 
    PERFORMANCE performance-options; 
    VAR variables ; 
    WEIGHT variable ; 

The HPCANDISC procedure is a high-performance procedure that performs canonical discriminant analysis. 
It is a high-performance version of the CANDISC procedure in SAS/STAT software. PROC HPCANDISC runs in 
either single-machine mode or distributed mode. 

Note: Distributed mode requires SAS High-Performance Statistics.
